description:
&lt;p&gt;NECS works across the UK to support health and social care customers in meeting strategic and operational challenges, to improve outcomes and increase efficiency. We deliver a diverse range of services to organisations working within health and social care across the North of England and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NECS combines specialist skills and expertise with scale and resilience to achieve required results. Many of our people have extensive NHS and public sector experience and we combine core NHS values with a sharp focus on customer care and a relentless pursuit of continuous improvement. We very much see ourselves as a key partner in the future success of the healthcare system and we take our share of the responsibility for shaping effective delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our digital, data and technology specialists work with internal teams in NECS and external customers to drive forward the technology agenda within health and care and is key to NECS’ strategic plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Applications Development Team is made up of multi-disciplined individuals working principally within the .Net Core and Framework, using C#.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Front end development is a combination of the usual HTML, CSS and JavaScript; with Angular and Bootstrap as the preferred client-side frameworks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Azure DevOps is our tool of choice for backlog management, source control, CI/CD, test plans, and documentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Main purpose of role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are searching for a talented Junior Developer to join our development team. You will be working alongside experienced developers on our various projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work alongside an evolving team, to design, build, test, support and maintain a range of software solutions on behalf of NECS and its customer base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will assist users and handle support requests received in to the team ensuring all response times are adhered to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate a willingness to learn and advance in their career and must be flexible in their outlook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Activities include&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To develop, test, maintain and support the systems and solutions currently in use and those subsequently deployed by the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the day to day operation of the organisation’s systems and applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for ensuring the timely resolution of incidents and fulfilment of customer requests, providing advice and guidance in accordance with standard operational procedures and agreed performance criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing web applications using .Net technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C# and SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frontend skills including HTML/CSS/JavaScript&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educated to Degree level or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relevant training in digital applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MVC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Web API, Web Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unit Testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source control such as Git&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working in an Agile/SCRUM environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree level education or equivalent qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of working with NECS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Visual Studio (MSDN) Subscription and associated benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the latest Microsoft technologies and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous development and accreditation opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous holiday allowance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice car scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to NHS discounts with major retailers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Durham / Sheffield / Chester.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There may be occasions where travel is required such as customer meetings or other NECS sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visa Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are unable to offer sponsorship for this role for any candidate that requires a visa to work in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
